rounds.event: Cold War: The Truman Doctrine is proclaimed to help stem the spread of Communism.
births: Peter Harry Carstensen, German educator and politician
Mitt Romney, American businessman and politician, 70th Governor of Massachusetts

rounds.event: Great Depression: Franklin D. Roosevelt addresses the nation for the first time as President of the United States. This is also the first of his "fireside chats".
The future capital of Australia is officially named Canberra.
births: Yashwantrao Chavan, Indian politician, 5th Deputy Prime Minister of India
Agathe von Trapp, Hungarian-American singer and author

rounds.event: The United States suspends travel from Europe due to the COVID-19 pandemic.
North Korea announces that it will withdraw from the Treaty on the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons and refuses to allow inspectors access to its nuclear sites.
